19:11.515 --> 19:12.600
I'm sorry.

19:12.687 --> 19:14.280
Sorry, yeah, I'm a teacher here,

19:14.367 --> 19:17.501
and, uh, things have gotten
out of control here today,

19:17.588 --> 19:19.242
but we're really proud
of our students.

19:19.329 --> 19:22.735
They staged a walkout
to express their opinions

19:22.822 --> 19:25.119
about the content of
the curriculum. Now, come on.

19:25.206 --> 19:27.234
How-how often do you hear
high school students

19:27.321 --> 19:30.040
caring that much about
what they're reading in class

19:30.206 --> 19:31.946
that they stage a protest?

19:32.540 --> 19:34.750
So, this was
school-sanctioned, Mister...?

19:34.837 --> 19:37.165
Uh, Solloway.

19:37.252 --> 19:39.514
Um... yeah.

19:39.601 --> 19:41.752
Yeah, that's what
Compton Academy's all about.

19:41.839 --> 19:43.376
You know,
we try to raise...

19:43.463 --> 19:48.078
and create engaged students
and-and-and responsible citizens

19:48.165 --> 19:49.829
to lead the next
generation.

19:49.930 --> 19:52.244
So, Mr. Solloway,
what can you tell us

19:52.331 --> 19:54.874
about the specifics
of the students' demands?

19:54.961 --> 19:57.994
Well, they, uh...
they weren't too specific,

19:58.081 --> 20:00.036
but essentially,
they want a-a...

20:00.123 --> 20:01.583
a more inclusive curriculum.

20:01.947 --> 20:03.626
There was fucking
riot police, Helen.

20:03.713 --> 20:04.970
What was I supposed to do?

20:05.057 --> 20:07.137
Yes, I'm still coming over.

20:08.571 --> 20:10.235
It's saying an hour 20.

20:11.391 --> 20:13.728
Fine, they just eat late.
Who cares?

20:15.454 --> 20:16.768
Okay, fine.

20:16.855 --> 20:18.444
I don't teach till ten tomorrow.

20:18.531 --> 20:20.986
I'll come over,
and I'll take them to school.

20:21.415 --> 20:22.860
Well, if that's
the only fucking way

20:22.947 --> 20:24.548
I'm gonna see
my own kids, Helen,

20:24.635 --> 20:26.431
then I don't mind driving.

20:26.978 --> 20:28.417
Thanks. Yeah, thanks a lot.

20:28.504 --> 20:29.946
That's really generous.

20:30.416 --> 20:32.194
Bunch of us are heading
to this bar over

20:32.281 --> 20:33.421
- in Inglewood...
- Yes.

20:33.508 --> 20:34.921
Awesome, dude.

20:35.008 --> 20:36.275
It's kind of
a divey place.

20:36.362 --> 20:38.217
Hey, when you say "us,"
do you mean just the teachers

20:38.304 --> 20:40.051
- or the administrators, too?
- Not to worry.

20:40.138 --> 20:42.298
She never comes slumming
with us plebes.

20:45.823 --> 20:47.369
With something like this,

20:47.600 --> 20:49.250
the police presence
and everything,

20:49.337 --> 20:51.414
there is zero chance
she doesn't get fired.

20:51.501 --> 20:53.640
We'll see. There's still
a lot of people on that board

20:53.727 --> 20:55.890
- who really love her.
- Oh, not after today.

20:55.977 --> 20:57.627
They're finally gonna realize
they should have

20:57.714 --> 21:00.064
promoted you in the first place.

21:01.209 --> 21:02.819
I thought she did
pretty fucking well.

21:02.906 --> 21:03.984
Shh!

21:04.185 --> 21:05.978
Hey, look, it's on TV.

21:10.612 --> 21:13.286
The variety that we see in the
student body being reflected

21:13.373 --> 21:14.554
in the curriculum,
that's what they really...

21:14.641 --> 21:16.109
Well done, dude.

21:16.196 --> 21:18.198
Did I say I was principal?

21:18.460 --> 21:20.790
Congratulations
on your promotion.

21:21.774 --> 21:22.947
Janelle.

21:23.068 --> 21:25.112
What's everybody drinking?

21:25.374 --> 21:27.220
Y'all were great today.

21:27.549 --> 21:29.095
Let me buy
the next round.

21:29.901 --> 21:32.697
Uh, you know, Janelle,
I think we're okay.

21:32.784 --> 21:34.460
Joel just got us
another round,

21:34.547 --> 21:36.345
and tomorrow's
a school day, so...

21:36.541 --> 21:38.485
Very responsible.

21:39.245 --> 21:42.345
Okay, well,
if you change your minds...

21:42.869 --> 21:44.371
let me know.

21:49.065 --> 21:51.361
I thought you said
she never came.

21:51.582 --> 21:53.900
I guess she needed a drink.

22:02.334 --> 22:03.875
Excuse me.

22:06.915 --> 22:09.171
Is anybody
buying you a drink?

22:09.531 --> 22:12.234
I took care of myself.
Thank you.

22:14.040 --> 22:15.532
Hey.

22:17.055 --> 22:19.710
I wanted to apologize again.

22:20.966 --> 22:22.188
For what?

22:22.636 --> 22:25.013
Usurping my title?

22:25.600 --> 22:26.815
What can I get you?

22:26.902 --> 22:28.492
Uh, whatever
she's having.

22:28.635 --> 22:30.804
Whiskey, Jameson. Two?

22:31.013 --> 22:32.682
No, just, uh...
another one for her

22:32.804 --> 22:33.992
and a seltzer.

22:34.446 --> 22:35.956
Thanks.

22:37.081 --> 22:38.859
I was just
trying to help.

22:40.539 --> 22:42.271
I wasn't asking for your help.

22:42.358 --> 22:43.771
I had it under control.

22:44.562 --> 22:45.963
You did?

22:47.727 --> 22:49.075
Same card
you've been using?

22:49.162 --> 22:52.023
Uh... no, baby.

22:52.590 --> 22:55.007
Uh, this next round's
on my friend.

22:55.665 --> 22:57.640
And pour yourself
something nice.

22:57.727 --> 22:59.041
On him, too.

22:59.133 --> 23:00.578
Keep the change.

23:02.422 --> 23:04.710
You know, you don't have
to sit here and babysit me.

23:04.797 --> 23:06.542
You can go back to your friends.

23:09.790 --> 23:11.789
I'm not sure I can, actually.

23:12.485 --> 23:14.086
Maybe not.

23:15.553 --> 23:17.023
And they're not my friends.

23:17.110 --> 23:18.273
Mine, either.

23:19.688 --> 23:21.697
This is all gonna blow over,
you know that?

23:21.784 --> 23:23.118
You think?

23:23.776 --> 23:26.075
I was on the phone
all afternoon with the board,

23:26.162 --> 23:27.796
fighting to keep my job.

23:28.465 --> 23:30.302
Then I come here to mend fences,

23:30.389 --> 23:32.804
and most of my staff

23:32.891 --> 23:35.109
won't even let me
buy them a drink.

23:38.169 --> 23:42.023
And then I... when I think about
what could have happened today,

23:42.440 --> 23:44.968
how badly it could have gone...

23:49.080 --> 23:52.016
So, tell me, how is this
all gonna blow over?

23:54.509 --> 23:56.430
Here's the thing
with your staff.

23:56.542 --> 23:57.710
They're young.

23:57.797 --> 23:58.928
They're children.

23:59.015 --> 24:00.134
Right.

24:00.779 --> 24:03.282
And like children,
they want to be listened to.

24:03.639 --> 24:05.243
They want to feel heard.

24:06.084 --> 24:09.828
And sometimes, in your...

24:10.353 --> 24:13.318
staff meetings, you seem like

24:13.405 --> 24:15.018
you don't really value
their opinions.

24:15.105 --> 24:16.225
I don't.

24:16.522 --> 24:17.898
Well, they know that.

24:17.998 --> 24:19.477
That's why they hate you.

24:19.775 --> 24:21.306
Wow.

24:21.524 --> 24:24.118
You really don't
need this job, do you?

24:29.181 --> 24:31.489
You know, at my
old school, Marshall,

24:31.576 --> 24:33.039
I was beloved.

24:34.087 --> 24:35.789
Like, seriously.

24:36.900 --> 24:40.282
Students fighting
to have lunch in my office,

24:40.657 --> 24:42.889
girls coming in to cry

24:42.976 --> 24:45.978
over whatever fool
was breaking their hearts.

24:47.133 --> 24:48.827
I'd do this Beyoncé thing

24:48.914 --> 24:51.469
every year at homecoming
that slayed.

24:51.736 --> 24:53.290
I'm sure.

24:55.628 --> 25:00.071
But when this job opened up,
I fought my ass off for it.

25:00.519 --> 25:02.719
At a public school
like Marshall,

25:02.824 --> 25:05.282
real progress is impossible.

25:05.498 --> 25:07.292
But at a charter,
you have autonomy.

25:07.379 --> 25:08.782
You set the agenda.

25:09.005 --> 25:10.774
I thought to myself,
here's my chance

25:10.861 --> 25:12.235
to actually make a difference

25:12.322 --> 25:13.961
with the kids
nobody else wanted.

25:14.384 --> 25:16.868
You know what happens
at a school like Marshall?

25:17.441 --> 25:19.102
They take in these kids,

25:19.189 --> 25:21.389
they keep them
till the fall census,

25:21.476 --> 25:23.254
they collect money
from the state,

25:23.341 --> 25:25.493
and then they dump
their sorry asses.

25:25.993 --> 25:27.349
They don't suspend.

25:27.436 --> 25:28.681
They expel.

25:29.462 --> 25:32.883
Those are the kids we picked up
at Compton Academy this year.

25:34.974 --> 25:36.446
And you know what?

25:36.563 --> 25:39.149
They need some
fucking discipline.

25:40.861 --> 25:42.100
And you know what else?

25:42.187 --> 25:43.657
If I were a white guy...

25:43.771 --> 25:45.341
if I were you, Noah Solloway,

25:45.428 --> 25:48.078
with your... with your looks
and your credentials,

25:48.857 --> 25:50.607
nobody would
give a shit about

25:50.694 --> 25:52.639
my disciplinary
practices.

25:52.726 --> 25:55.936
They would congratulate me
for having balls.

25:56.290 --> 25:57.814
But because I'm me,

25:57.901 --> 26:01.689
I'm expected to be
collaborative.

26:02.749 --> 26:04.360
And if I'm not...

26:04.447 --> 26:07.208
if I dare to say

26:07.924 --> 26:10.157
I have 20 fucking years

26:10.244 --> 26:12.275
of experience
in this business...

26:12.758 --> 26:15.595
I was teaching
when most of you

26:15.682 --> 26:16.788
were in driver's ed,

26:16.875 --> 26:19.751
so maybe... just maybe
I actually know

26:19.838 --> 26:21.478
what the fuck I'm doing.

26:26.375 --> 26:27.751
How's Anton?

26:27.963 --> 26:29.915
Is he okay after today?

26:30.516 --> 26:31.971
I hope so.

26:32.420 --> 26:34.103
He's with his dad.

26:35.803 --> 26:37.888
Yeah, mine are with their mom.

26:38.081 --> 26:39.225
You have kids?

26:39.312 --> 26:40.349
Mmm.

26:40.644 --> 26:42.407
Two boys, two girls.

26:42.574 --> 26:44.251
Damn, you're busy.

26:44.956 --> 26:47.125
Well, the older ones
are away at school now,

26:47.212 --> 26:50.055
and the... the younger two,
they live with my ex.

26:50.142 --> 26:51.556
That's why I'm in L.A.

26:51.643 --> 26:53.030
She came out with her boyfriend.

26:53.117 --> 26:54.501
I followed.

26:54.722 --> 26:56.458
