Mm-hmm.
Vik did very well.

48:08.963 --> 48:11.868
He's worked so hard
his whole life.

48:12.094 --> 48:13.966
From when he was
a little boy,

48:14.053 --> 48:17.133
he just pushed himself
and pushed himself.

48:17.553 --> 48:21.555
Abdul and I were so worried
that he would never slow down,

48:21.647 --> 48:23.680
never enjoy his success.

48:23.887 --> 48:26.110
But now,
finally, he can.

48:26.601 --> 48:28.645
And I am so happy for him.

48:35.105 --> 48:36.954
Priya, I need your help.

48:43.488 --> 48:45.448
Vik is very sick.

48:46.705 --> 48:47.977
And he won't
listen to me.

48:48.064 --> 48:49.415
He's refusing treatment.

48:49.502 --> 48:51.969
But he has to do something.
If he waits...

48:54.917 --> 48:57.594
And I know how much
you and Abdul mean to him

48:57.892 --> 48:59.545
and how much he wants
to make you proud,

48:59.632 --> 49:01.649
so I just... I just
thought that maybe if it...

49:01.736 --> 49:03.032
if it came from you...

49:18.938 --> 49:20.649
Thank you for telling me.

49:49.147 --> 49:51.899
- Hi.
- My mom's not feeling well.

49:52.981 --> 49:54.030
Oh.

49:54.117 --> 49:56.077
She's got
a bad headache.

49:56.355 --> 49:57.532
So...

49:57.619 --> 49:58.720
we're leaving early.

49:58.807 --> 50:00.122
No. Oh, don't leave.

50:00.209 --> 50:02.024
I-I have Advil, I think.

50:02.111 --> 50:05.144
No, a little rest
is what I need.

50:07.689 --> 50:09.144
I'm gonna walk them out.

50:09.570 --> 50:11.134
I'm gonna come with you.

50:11.221 --> 50:12.298
Oh, sorry.

50:13.387 --> 50:15.363
You're sure you know
how to get home from here?

50:15.458 --> 50:16.847
I can write down
directions.

50:16.934 --> 50:19.517
If we get lost again,
we'll stop at a petrol station.

50:19.604 --> 50:21.548
Dad, it'll take two seconds.
Just let...

50:21.635 --> 50:23.341
The car is here, Priya.

50:23.814 --> 50:25.199
We'll see you soon, Vikram.

50:25.286 --> 50:27.246
Okay. Good night, Mom.

50:35.748 --> 50:37.597
Priya. Priya.

50:37.814 --> 50:39.636
Did you not hear
what I said?

50:40.113 --> 50:42.050
Vik has cancer.

50:42.137 --> 50:45.839
He has late-stage cancer,
and he needs to get treatment.

50:45.926 --> 50:47.357
Please, I don't know...

50:54.863 --> 50:56.785
I don't know
what else to do.

50:58.137 --> 50:59.825
Please.

51:04.564 --> 51:07.410
You're going to figure
this out, Vikram.

51:07.536 --> 51:09.371
You always do.

51:10.686 --> 51:12.324
Thanks, Ma.

51:27.980 --> 51:29.651
Hand me the water.

51:42.459 --> 51:45.232
Can we please talk
about this like adults?

51:59.481 --> 52:01.878
I asked you
to do one thing.

52:03.004 --> 52:05.208
One thing.

52:06.105 --> 52:09.324
I asked you not
to tell my parents.

52:09.571 --> 52:11.141
- And what did you do?
- I had to.

52:11.228 --> 52:12.988
She's your mother.

52:13.168 --> 52:16.880
Ho-Ho-Honestly, I don't...
I don't understand your family.

52:16.967 --> 52:18.579
It's like you're all in denial.

52:18.666 --> 52:20.714
Is it just
a way of life for you?

52:21.928 --> 52:23.574
Oh, my God.

52:25.706 --> 52:28.666
You really don't understand
anything, do you?

52:30.856 --> 52:33.480
You might as well have
grown up in a fucking castle.

52:33.567 --> 52:37.105
You are such a privileged,
entitled little...

52:46.136 --> 52:48.542
You want to criticize
my parents?

52:51.048 --> 52:54.604
What the fuck have you ever
had to sacrifice for your kids?

52:57.527 --> 52:59.377
My dad was a doctor.

53:01.076 --> 53:02.542
A cardiologist.

53:03.011 --> 53:07.101
Like, a really respected
young doctor back in Beirut.

53:07.188 --> 53:09.776
And now he's
a fucking dry cleaner

53:10.094 --> 53:12.338
because he wanted
to raise me here.

53:14.746 --> 53:16.737
They never
took vacations

53:16.824 --> 53:18.979
or-or went home
for weddings

53:19.066 --> 53:22.151
or births or funerals,

53:23.480 --> 53:26.745
because every last scrap
of money was for Vikram.

53:28.102 --> 53:30.187
For Vikram's education.

53:31.933 --> 53:35.799
So they could send me
to college and medical school.

53:37.426 --> 53:40.843
They denied
themselves everything

53:41.045 --> 53:43.446
to make me into something
they could be proud of.

53:43.533 --> 53:47.667
So yeah, yeah, denial
is a way of life for them,

53:47.754 --> 53:50.851
and all I wanted,
all I asked of you,

53:50.938 --> 53:52.821
was to spare them
the pain of knowing

53:52.908 --> 53:54.589
that all that
was for nothing.

53:54.739 --> 53:59.003
I mean, couldn't they get
one night, just one night,

53:59.739 --> 54:03.113
to enjoy what all of
their sacrifice had achieved?

54:03.296 --> 54:06.386
Don't say it was
all for nothing.

54:06.473 --> 54:07.564
We don't know that.

54:07.651 --> 54:09.847
There are treatments.
There are trials.

54:09.934 --> 54:12.829
You're not a fucking
doctor, Helen. I am.

54:12.916 --> 54:14.996
- I know.
- No, you don't.

54:16.309 --> 54:19.066
I have pancreatic cancer.

54:20.439 --> 54:23.253
And those trials
aren't promising.

54:23.494 --> 54:24.878
They're desperate.

54:25.786 --> 54:28.972
Because there is
no real treatment for this.

54:29.952 --> 54:31.777
There is no cure.

54:32.652 --> 54:34.043
No hope.

54:36.411 --> 54:38.582
I am going to die.

54:57.369 --> 54:59.625
I've spent
my entire career

54:59.712 --> 55:02.430
giving false hope
to my patients,

55:04.149 --> 55:06.805
and I am not gonna
fucking do it for you.

55:11.856 --> 55:13.522
I'm sorry.

55:17.462 --> 55:18.963
Vik, I'm really sorry.

55:19.050 --> 55:21.344
I, uh... I fucked up.

55:23.689 --> 55:24.865
What do you want me to do?

55:24.952 --> 55:26.243
I told you.

55:30.801 --> 55:32.493
I want to have a baby.

55:35.978 --> 55:38.194
If you really want
to do something for me,

55:38.281 --> 55:39.469
you can do that.

56:36.376 --> 56:38.302
We're so lucky
to be here.

56:38.389 --> 56:41.196
I heard this guy's
success rate is insane.

56:47.063 --> 56:48.610
Can I ask you a question?

56:48.772 --> 56:50.009
Sure.

56:50.314 --> 56:52.813
Who was president
the year you were born?

56:53.822 --> 56:54.980
